  "texts": [
    "Recently, various defense mechanisms have been proposed, which can be categorized into two main types: (1) Black-box defenses, which do not require access to LLM's parameters.",
    "Examples include adding an extra prompt to make the model aware of attacks (Toyer et al., 2023; Yi et al., 2023) and placing special delimiters around external content (Yi et al., 2023); (2) White-box defenses, which necessitate access to and modification of LLM parameters.",
    "Strategies include fine-tuning the LLM with attack cases (Yi et al., 2023; Piet et al., 2023), replacing command words with encoded versions and instructing the LLM to accept only these encoded commands (Suo, 2024), and separating prompts and data into two channels using a secure front-end for formatting alongside a specially trained LLM (Chen et al., 2024).",
    "However, these studies primarily focus on basic scenarios where instructions and data are straightforwardly concatenated and input into the LLM.",
    "The implementation of these defense strategies in tool-integrated LLM agents and their effectiveness in more complex scenarios are areas that warrant further exploration in the future."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Examples include adding an extra prompt to make the model aware of attacks (Toyer et al., 2023; Yi et al., 2023) and placing special delimiters around external content (Yi et al., 2023); (2) White-box defenses, which necessitate access to and modification of LLM parameters.",
    "Strategies include fine-tuning the LLM with attack cases (Yi et al., 2023; Piet et al., 2023), replacing command words with encoded versions and instructing the LLM to accept only these encoded commands (Suo, 2024), and separating prompts and data into two channels using a secure front-end for formatting alongside a specially trained LLM (Chen et al., 2024)."
